HEADWORD: Odontolite
<hw>O*don"to*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Odonto-</ets> + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A fossil tooth colored a bright blue by phosphate of iron. It is
used as an imitation of turquoise, and hence called <altname>bone
turquoise</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Odontology</ent>⟦br⟧
